edu.ucla.sspace.text

Interface ParsedDocument

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Document
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LabeledParsedDocument
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LabeledParsedStringDocument

    public interface ParsedDocument
extends Document
    An abstraction for a document that has been (or will be) dependency parsed to generate an accompanying parse tree of its contents.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      DependencyTreeNode[] parsedDocument()
      Returns the dependency tree of the next document as a sequence of DependencyTreeNode instances.
      String prettyPrintText()
      Returns a pretty-printed version of the document's text without any of the parsing-related annotation and using heuristics to appropriately space punctuation, quotes, and contractions.
      String text()
      Returns the text of the parsed document without any of the parsing-related annotation, with each parsed token separated by whitespace.

    • Method Detail

      • parsedDocument

        DependencyTreeNode[] parsedDocument()

      • text

        String text()
        Returns the text of the parsed document without any of the parsing-related annotation, with each parsed token separated by whitespace.

      • prettyPrintText

        String prettyPrintText()
        Returns a pretty-printed version of the document's text without any of the parsing-related annotation and using heuristics to appropriately space punctuation, quotes, and contractions. This methods is intended as only a useful way to displaying the document's text in a more readable format than text(), but makes no claims as to reproducing the original surface form of the document prior to parsing.
